title: New England Fish Chowder
summary: New England Fish Chowder requires roughly 45 minutes from start to finish. This recipe makes 5 servings with 16436027 calories, 1448057g of protein, and 1136248g of fat each. For $27829.98 per serving, this recipe covers 92% of your daily requirements of vitamins and minerals. 307 people have made this recipe and would make it again. It is brought to you by Simply Recipes. Head to the store and pick up bay leaf, corned beef hash march 18, onions, and a few other things to make it today. To use up the lemon pie filling you could follow this main course with the Lemon Pie Bars as a dessert. It works well as a main course. Overall, this recipe earns a good spoonacular score of 43%. winePairing.pairingText: Pinot Grigio, Gruener Veltliner, and Pinot Noir are great choices for Fish. Fish is as diverse as wine, so it's hard to pick wines that go with every fish. A crisp white wine, such as a pinot grigio or Grüner Veltliner, will suit any delicately flavored white fish. Meaty, strongly flavored fish such as salmon and tuna can even handle a light red wine, such as a pinot noir. One wine you could try is Tramin Pinot Grigio. It has 4.4 out of 5 stars and a bottle costs about 11 dollars.

productMatches.title: Tramin Pinot Grigio
productMatches.description: Bright yellow in color with coppery reflections and clear fruit aromas of pear, citrus, honeysuckle, tropical fruits and light spices. Firm, velvety and rich on the palate, with well-integrated acidity. A very round and satisfying wine. Recommended with fish antipasti, risotto with asparagus, omelets and pasta
